deck: The Recluse is a member of the Front Line, a century ago he was a big game hunter that toured Africa but received a curse that turned him into a spider-like monster.
description:
Origin

Before becoming donning the mask and becoming a superhero, the man that would become the Recluse was originally a big game hunter. While in Africa he received an ancient African curse that turned him in a spider-like monster. His only way to alleviate his affliction was to eat the hearts of other humans.

Thanks to his powers he stopped aging and took numerous identities. He started his superhero career possibly in even donning a mask, calling himself Doc Spider to fight crime during America's Prohibition era.

He eventually found his way to Toronto where he teamed up with heroes to stop the V'Ran invasion. The Recluse became one of the founding members of Front Line.

When the hero Crosswind came into the fold of the Front Line, unlike many of his teammates, the Recluse was suspicious about him from the beginning. He was unable to find any hardcore proof of Crosswind's origins.

The Recluse caught Gaijin and Crosswind attempting to steal the team's files, he initially accused Gaijin of treachery, but apologized when she revealed her adopted brother was kidnapped and being held for ransom. The Recluse, Gaijin and Crosswind searched for him, tracking him to an abandoned warehouse. To cover more ground the trio split up, unfortunately the Recluse began to suffer from his curse, into to alleviate his pain, he called his assistant Samantha, who directed him to a bar where he might feed. However on the way he found Kayoto's barely alive. And to make things worse the V'Ran had returned with three new giant bio-mech and began terrorizing the city. Faced with a dilemma and his hunger, Samantha urged him to feed on Kayoto's heart as he was a criminal and would be doing him a mercy as his condition was far beyond help. Regaining his humanity and a clear mind, Recluse realized the attack on Kayoto was consistent to a man being spun and flung to the air. He then realized it to be Crosswind, but was unable to determine why Crosswind would do such as thing.

Crosswind appeared behind and proceeded to attack him, however their fight was postponed when the saw civilians in danger of a burning building. Both silently agreed to hold off to rescue them. Once the people cleared, the two heroes brawled. Recluse demanded why Crosswind murdered Gaijin's brother, and what was his angle, only to be met with taunts by his former teammate. Crosswind told Recluse it was useless and that he had seen Recluse devour Gaijin's heart, and no matter what he could say he would turn the Front Line against him. When Crosswind said he would kill Samantha once he put an end to him, Recluse attacked him viciously damaging Crosswind's armor, only to discover Crosswind powers came from himself and not his suit. Crosswind proceeded to beat the Recluse to a pulp, until he heard a scream of a young boy and his cat clinging to dear life. Crosswind abandoned his task to saving the two, but was killed by debris.

After the invasion, the Recluse asked the team not to reveal Crosswind's death to the public. He gave them an explanation that he wished to locate Crosswind's family, however using Crosswind's communication helmet he tracked his employer, Ray Fournier. After threatening the police inspector why he targeted Front Line, Recluse learned that Fournier's family were casualties from the first V'Ran attack and that the inspector was furious of the heroes lack of humility when they soaked in the limelight of their debut and their lack of concern for the innocents.

Recluse realizing the man was right about Front Line's hubris, released Fournier, he told the inspector that he would make Kayoto's death one of the many deaths from the second invasion, and the he would be working for him.

After Luminary left Earth to discover more about her powers, Recluse succeeded her as leader of Front Line. He never told the team of Crosswind's deception but instead martyred him as a hero. Taking Fourier's word to heart he turned Front Lines direction into saving the innocence as a priority.

Powers & Abilities

Intelligence: The Recluse appears to be a master detective and skilled in tracking.

Wall Crawling: The Recluse is able to stick to walls like a spider due to his hybrid nature.

Wall Crawling: He has limited ability to extend his fingers into claws, which are capable of ripping through metal.

Transformation: As part of his curse the Recluse turns into a humanoid spider creature, unless he devours the hearts of humans on a daily basis. In order to function in society, Errol kidnaps criminals that have escape justice through the legal proceedings, and other scum that would not be missed to feed on them
name: Recluse

deck: Gregor Markov, brother to Brion Markov (Geo-Force) is the current King of Markovia. He is known for implementing democratic reforms in his country.
description:
Storyline

Gregor Markov is the son of King Viktor of Markovia. His brother is Brion Markov, who would become the super-hero Geo-Force, and his illegitimate sister is Tara Markov, who would become the super-hero Terra.

Prince Gregor's father King Viktor died during a revolution staged by Baron Bedlam. Gregor became King. His brother Prince Brion used scientist Helga Jace to develop super-powers, making him into the super-hero Geo-Force. Gregor went into battle against Bedlam's army hopelessly outnumbered, manning a tank. Markovia was saved by the intervention of Batman and the Outsiders. Geo-Force threw Bedlam to the people, who executed him. Gregor was sad to see Brion leave for Gotham City with the others. He told the people that his first act was sending Prince Brion to learn and study in America.

Bedlam returns from the dead to stage another coup, and kidnaps Gregor's fiancee Princess Ilona. Reporter Joan Lincoln tries to help King Gregor get his story out, but no news networks are interested. Bedlam attacks Castle Markov with the Masters of Disaster and captures King Gregor. Gregor, Ilona, and Lincoln are all sentenced to death by firing squad. The Outsiders rally the Markovian army to attack Bedlam, and Geo-Force rescues his brother at the last moment. For crimes against Markovia, Geo-Force decapitates Baron Bedlam. King Gregor gives the Markovian Medal of Honor to all of the Outsiders. He asks them to become Markovia's unofficial "agents of change," dealing with threats that world government is forced to ignore. King Gregor has a beautiful wedding ceremony to Princess Ilona. The Outsiders accept his proposal.

The Outsiders approach King Gregor again when they're tracking Bad Samaritan. Gregor provides them with fake identification to help them go undercover in the Soviet Union. When the Outsiders are kidnapped by President Bentama, Gregor is angry that he cannot intervene for political reasons. Gregor is threatened when the Masters of Disaster escape Markovian prison, but they decide he is worth more as a messenger to Geo-Force. Lincoln interviews Gregor again when his country is electing a new prime minister.

Psycho-Pirate poses as Baron Bedlam to stage another coup in Markovia. Gregor and Ilona are imprisoned in the dungeon. They are rescued by the Outsiders working together with Infinity, Inc.. Gregor calls the Outsiders back to Markovia when the secret of their connection is revealed to the world. The U.S. government threatens to withdraw all support from Markovia unless they give up the names of the Outsiders. Brion and Gregor have a huge argument. Helga Jace uses poison gas to assassinate King Gregor while he is meeting with U.S. government officials. Brion becomes the next King of Markovia. During the coronation ceremony, Jace brainwashes Ilona to accuse Brion of murdering Gregor. Ilona also reveals that she is carrying Gregor's true heir.
name: Gregor Markov

deck: Member of Justice-9 on Earth-36 and homage to Big Bang Comics's homage to Aquaman.
description:
Origin

The aquatic member of the Justice-9 from Earth-36.

Creation

Mer-man was created by Grant Morrison and Evan Shaner. His first appearance was in The Multiversity Guidebook #1.

History

Mer-man is based on the Atomic Sub, the Big Bang Comics analogue of Aquaman. He was a briliant scientist who discovered a special chemical formula fro a synthetic blood that allowed for underwater adaptation and after an accident, his mind was placed inside a near indestructible cyborg body, fueled by the formula.

The Multiversity Guidebook

Mer-Man appears in this issue as member of Justice-9, the Earth-36 analogue of Round Table of America (which is in turn based on Justice League of America). Earth-36 is an analogue of the Big Bang Comics Earth.

Powers & Abilities

Not all of Mer-man's powers have been revealed, but they resemble Aquaman's and the Atomic Sub's powers.

Superhuman Strength

Mer-man possesses superhuman strength.

Superhuman Durability

Mer-man possesses a cyborg body with superhuman durability.

Superhuman Swimming Speed

Mer-man can swim at superhuman speeds.

Superhuman Senses

Mer-man possesses superhuman sight, due to his cyborg body.

Underwater Adaptation

He can function normally underwater and is able to withstand the high pressures and extreme temperatures of the deep. He can also function on land normally.

Flight

He can fly at high speeds, with the aid of his cyborg modifications.

Sonar

He has the ability to track objects underwater with the sonar in his hands.

Longevity

He is long lived and his cyborg body doesn't age.

Expert Scientist

He is a genius scientist that worked against the Nazis, and has created a number of scientific marvels, like his cyborg body and synthetic blood.

Weapons and Equipment

Helmet

He wears a distinct helmet that only exposes the front of his face, similar to the Atomic Sub.
name: Mer-Man
